BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (18): ALBANIA (KORCE), OVINE, SEROTYPE 4, OIE
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 12 Sep 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2014; 27(38) OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16052


Bluetongue, Albania
-------------------
Information received on [and dated] 12 Sep 2014 from Dr Shpresa Arbi, Chief Veterinary Officer Director of Veterinary Directorate, Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture, Rural Development and Water Administration, Tirana, Albania

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 13 Aug 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 25 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2003
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 3
Outbreak 1: Qender Leskovik, Qender Leskovik, Kolonje, Korce
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Aug 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Goats / 30 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 250 / 25 / 4 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Goats / 0 percent / 0 percent / - / 0 percent
Sheep / 10 percent / 1.6 percent / 16 percent / 1.6 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); dipping/spraying; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Control of arthropods

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Food Safety and Veterinary Institute (national laboratory) / Sheep / antibody detection ELISA / 25 Aug 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Bluetongue serotype 4 continues to spread in the regional area. Albania now joins Romania, Bulgaria, the former Yugoslav Republic (FYR) of Macedonia, Greece and Turkey.

A map showing the distribution of outbreaks can be seen at http://tinyurl.com/kvrhpms. The map includes all reported serotypes for the selected time period (January to September 2014). (Note: to see the region of interest in more detail, click on the map to zoom in.) - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2769813,41421.]
